					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I know smkd is going to disagree with me, but I don't understand why developers waste their already very limited time being obsessive compulsing about memory size to gain a trivial amount of memory they don't even use. 
<br />
<br />For instance, the draw_status_bar code in Super Mario World. They make an entire loop, just to load 7 registers. All it does is save 5 extra bytes that they eventually didn't used, at the cost of effort and speed. That short of a loop actually takes more effort, than writing it without the loop.</div>

					
